Restrictions were put in place on the St. George campus over the weekend out of an abundance of caution due to protests in the Queen’s Park area, but the campus was quiet. The #UofT campuses in Mississauga @UTM & Scarborough @UTSC were unaffected. (7/7)

Check the campus status website for any further changes before travelling. High priority info will be shared through the emergency alerts system (UTAlert). Register for UTAlert at: https://t.co/BDbXl5mUN1

The Campus Safety Communications Centre is open 24/7: 416-978-2222. (6/7)

The City of Toronto may keep some roads around the Queen’s Park area closed Sunday & Monday. Check the city’s road-closure website & give yourself more time to reach your destination. https://t.co/6xXV6oeS5s (5/7)

Vehicle access on campus will be restored & parking lots reopened Monday. These remain closed Sunday.

The shuttle bus between @UTM & St. George will operate normally Monday. (4/7)
The Robarts & Gerstein libraries, the Athletic Centre, Goldring Centre, Varsity Centre, & Hart House will reopen Monday as usual. They remain closed Sunday. (3/7)

Normal building access on the St. George campus will be restored Monday. Students, faculty, librarians, & staff are able to enter most facilities for regular activities Sunday using keys & security fobs. (2/7)

SUNDAY UPDATE: All #UofT activities will take place as originally planned Monday in accordance with the move to increased in-person learning, research, & work. As a reminder, students should refer to the info specific to each campus & Faculty here: https://t.co/NcSV0zaTrq (1/7)

#UofT will provide another update tomorrow as the situation evolves. High priority information will be shared through the emergency alerts system (UTAlert). Register for UTAlert: https://t.co/BDbXl5mUN1 
 
The Campus Safety Communications Centre is open 24/7: 416-978-2222. (5/5)

You will notice an increased police presence in the area around Queen’s Park; the City of Toronto has closed surrounding roads and parking.  
 
The U of T campuses in Mississauga @UTM and Scarborough @UTSC remain open. (4/5)

Out of an abundance of caution, the Robarts and Gerstein libraries, the Athletic Centre, Goldring Centre, Varsity Centre, and Hart House will remain closed over the weekend. Vehicle access on campus is restricted and on-campus parking lots are unavailable. (3/5)

The University is open but access to our buildings on the St. George campus remains restricted. Students, faculty, librarians, and staff are able to enter most facilities for regular activities using keys and security fobs. (2/5)
SATURDAY MORNING UPDATE: Members of the #UofT community are advised to avoid the Queen’s Park area this weekend and remain vigilant on the St. George campus due to the planned protests. (1/5)

Q: Which activities require full vaccination?

A: Vaccination is required for students in residence and for activities like music performance, varsity athletics, and educational placements. You’ll be required to declare your vaccination status before returning to campus. 3/4

Q: What about those who are not vaccinated?

A: If you’re not vaccinated, you will complete a COVID-19 rapid screening test at home twice a week. You need a negative result within 72 hours of coming to campus. 2/4

Q: Do you need to be vaccinated to be on campus?

A: #UofT will require all those intending to be on campus be fully vaccinated, similar to other universities. Students, staff and librarians returning to campus need to state their vaccination status on UCheck. 1/4
